  "style": "APA",
  "texts": [
    "Moreover, adaptive AI models can be developed that dynamically adjust to changes in an individual's sensory preferences over time.",
    "For example, olfactory preferences may change with age, exposure to certain environments, or dietary changes (Doty and Kamath 2014).",
    "AI systems capable of learning and adapting to these shifts will provide more relevant and real-time insights, particularly in applications like personalized health monitoring, where olfactory patterns may indicate underlying health conditions.",
    "Integrating AI with wearable olfactory devices, such as smart nosebands or wearable olfactory interfaces, could further personalize these systems (McMillan 2021).",
    "These devices can continuously monitor an individual's olfactory responses and adjust to their preferences, offering a dynamic and tailored sensory experience."
  ],
  "correct_citations": [
    "For example, olfactory preferences may change with age, exposure to certain environments, or dietary changes (Doty and Kamath 2014)."
  ]
}